med part of a cultural resistance that stood against repression. As a writer, she found in the microcosm of the family and everyday events subtle entry into political, historical, and social issues. Heker’s stories examine the rituals people invent to relate to one another, especially girls and women, and they reveal how the consequences of tiny acts may be enormous. With charm, economy, and a close focus on the intimate, Heker has perfected the art of the glimpse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aShort stories, Spanishy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aFrance, Miranda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManguel, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030019804140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021370640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213706423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300213706/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY